{"id": "e84153f3d76d0a6a154926613db26a4dac0e3105dcc846f4d00d0aadfded2ecd", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:0", "text": "Do you need help setting up"}
{"id": "9020030346d952c71832314d85a451736285b82657e1de924ecfef4b5d16cdeb", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:1", "text": "Depth of Field in Maya"}
{"id": "9a190b6aa825ed978dfa8c5d018d356031051b705b4607d8a80bf03b196ed63a", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:2", "text": "in Maya or using"}
{"id": "6465a1bc3234c457f55a4652312d46c8bce577cc44e371d4ddcec5b35ef81579", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:3", "text": "Tilt-Shift in Maya"}
{"id": "76ef9587be0892bc5d3559eef73c71666bc67bf0e3d3e414be12d0a064077018", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:4", "text": "controls?"}
{"id": "4418edd3f828cb5b034066e403ebbb18e78e6375de150dc933c402e200ad8ed3", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:5", "text": "\"Bokeh\" is the name given to a side-effect of using Depth of Field where light sources or highlights form a shape where they are out of focus. The result is an almost \"glittery\" look that many people enjoy viewing."}
{"id": "f5b95e2a8c7ade4c657114358456698c28f5c529458d54825e0f89ad5fb3af00", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:6", "text": "In the below still from Pixar's"}
{"id": "49da71a8fd6ace865a0366c4d3203e6a9f374c0531c8682d627d1e357f91ad00", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:8", "text": "Blue Umbrella"}
{"id": "f795a5e2accbb88346543d94c307ec46468efa026746ada1e77fe1c33baf58d8", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:9", "text": "you can see light sources in the background have turned into circular blobs of colored light."}
{"id": "8f2f6cb82e9fbf5debd331661c49ba603412a76f8b369c330fb6be51e603b67a", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:10", "text": "Did you know that Bokeh effects are from a topic in optics called the Circle of Confusion?"}
{"id": "915a7c4d371b3f97180d4664cfd42537dcce2c40229ff5e781d8d960d151250e", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:11", "text": "They are available under the RenderMan Rollout in your camera Attribute Editor (AE) Panel."}
{"id": "4206ae62999872baa9a06e391ccdd8e6d6301a09802ee33fb03794c7477fe543", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:12", "text": "These controls are called"}
{"id": "6b70f7a055f981034e0ed0a4628653e652794a1474c1488e605b3b783964c229", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:13", "text": "Bokeh"}
{"id": "c098692138342beec4d3caacab3c13181499df42093b74af3fc3320e118075bd", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:14", "text": "in the menu."}
{"id": "4f98425292288336b6e354458b061d226da6dc7134695f94db07269f7f0c35ae", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:15", "text": "There are 4 controls and a convenient tooltip when you hover over the name or value fields. The controls from left to right and top to bottom are:"}
{"id": "6d19c53b978f5b7a02a9e0ef03a53d435631827258be53e6bc7d4d816d6c0f63", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:16", "text": "Number of"}
{"id": "2e27c47b6df26cd82b45b90385eac87bb6fb54385f86df92a8c244ec6ed90260", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:17", "text": "Sides:"}
{"id": "078bf2b864ecc8780730ef452f3835838cf4284d3a2dac1bf854d454428fda28", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:18", "text": "This determines the shape of the bokeh effect. If you choose fewer than three sides (triangle) the bokeh will be circular."}
{"id": "1968034b13f84d0c3e441fcc8b5f3ec7b75fcabdbcecb68177445498557d3e33", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:19", "text": "Angle"}
{"id": "a1abf1542b21888f2515ec4bbc5ebf576a5d040cb5f4216912766d2d40562723", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:20", "text": "in Degrees"}
{"id": "5e37a182b1ef1353ba45a28199d2059ab8bf72bb22bb02e25f8d25f20cee9a8b", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:22", "text": "This controls the angle where sides meet for non-circular bokeh shapes (Number of Sides is greater than 2)."}
{"id": "6d2a81f0afeb6766bb151972b2c37e7deb5627ecfc333dfc919c1481aadf767f", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:23", "text": "Roundness:"}
{"id": "08e2ee05a4f04531c0d8652c6c2ffd11cd5b6cff354cea8a7a139e2da8f6f59c", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:24", "text": "Values from 0 to 1 make the shape bow or flex outwards making it more rounded. Values from 0 to -1 bow inwards and make for sharper points."}
{"id": "f18f26870f635d476cf6b69f4cbc948e1692b6e05b9287e0284770182271cabd", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:25", "text": "Density:"}
{"id": "48d97d8244290e7ecdc1e8985ce277efce5d37b1ae00dce56a6d0060c21ab8a1", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:26", "text": "This controls the brightness across the bokeh shape. 0 to 1 makes it brighter at the outer edge like a catadrioptic lens (look it up, quite interesting). 0 to -1 makes it brighter in the center and falloff towards the edges."}
{"id": "3516c26efcc0a4431c68fe9fe959d7205712e47a69c32c18a6194d7eb8d6cee3", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:33", "text": "Below is an example using:"}
{"id": "e63c9e44b3de0a6f6a5700eb0343b743d15f3579e6190911efa5520d3f1ae827", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:28", "text": "Number of Sides = 6"}
{"id": "2672bee2060a61dd0046d02c3acb69d4c297c951515953b578b1f5b73bb6e416", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:29", "text": "Angle in Degrees = 33.33"}
{"id": "cdce5d433a7362e925d769bd08cf9efc5096ce6f7c1282c63445d6cc29d37445", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:36", "text": "Roundness = default (0.0)"}
{"id": "a6a537035c40af79291d8bc9616dbb10cad89436e0ee4ca02a889d74811dc0d9", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:31", "text": "Density = 1.0"}
{"id": "342623f0029fc71c7d4728a7df68908141eaa2f78714cdc24b3497138dd89646", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:32", "text": "Eyes on furthest alien = slightly creepy"}
{"id": "31cb0343e92462f184bebbf5650fff743ce77fb7e42d795a670bbf2343b45a6f", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:34", "text": "Number of Sides = 3"}
{"id": "1d095d695c641dfb3aeae2b83f88a8f0940802c08049244d92f494bfe8de9e46", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:35", "text": "Angle in Degrees = 60.0"}
{"id": "1cc3e85a5e0cd1fa62cf47d18d0f7f970f34c1ffe2be96efdecadeb97c5c15e4", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:37", "text": "Density = -0.5"}
{"id": "7a74b29cc68e5174f0ba53fab17e9743327140c79eed78a17b3861d5c660bf0f", "item_id": "4f68e4633e:38", "text": "Eyes on furthest alien = less creepy"}
